"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-dutch-deserve-backlash-after-letting-steven-van-de-velde-compete-in-paris\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 On Friday evening at the opening ceremony, IOC president Thomas Bach emerged from his sheltered seat, joined spectators in the rain (though an underling held an umbrella over his head) and told a worldwide audience what he wanted the viewers to hear:  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe all respect the same rules and each other.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 310, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 53, \"end\": 56, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3058270000775827e-31, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 67, \"end\": 78, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In our Olympic world, we all belong.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  This might (mostly) be true for games and sports.\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 401, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But in a larger sense, it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s not remotely true.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 450, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A sporting event with competitors from more than 200 countries also involves more than 200 sets of laws and more than 200 sets of cultural norms.\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 596, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Harmless acts in America are felonies in some other countries; transgressions that we find heinous, others view as misdemeanors.\", \"from\": 597, \"to\": 725, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This, as much as anything, explains why Steven van de Velde is here at the 2024 Paris Olympics, competing in beach volleyball for the Dutch.\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 867, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 774, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999795909488899, \"rank\": 2.0409467432898144e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}, {\"begin\": 861, \"end\": 866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9940577675347285, \"rank\": 0.005277742352251819, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2014, when van de Velde was 19, he flew to England to meet a 12-year-old girl he knew was 12, and he raped her.\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999795909488899, \"rank\": 2.0409467432898144e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}, {\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9856413321354742, \"rank\": 0.0141783463409592, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To be clear: He was notaccusedof raping her; he was tried, convicted, and sent to prison for 13 months.\", \"from\": 984, \"to\": 1087, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has acknowledged what he did.\", \"from\": 1088, \"to\": 1120, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The facts of the case are not in dispute, but a single word in this paragraph is.\", \"from\": 1121, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In England, he was guilty of rape.\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1214, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9856413321354742, \"rank\": 0.0141783463409592, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the Netherlands, he was guilty of fornication.\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1289, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1247, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.999968710661719, \"rank\": 3.1288944247629376e-05, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is not a case of semantics.\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is actually a reflection of Dutch laws governing sexual assault.\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1355, \"end\": 1360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9940577675347285, \"rank\": 0.005277742352251819, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A new, extremely overduesexual crimes bill was enactedin the Netherlands this month, by Dutch justice and security minister Dilan Ye\\u00c5\\u009filg\\u00c3\\u00b6z-Zegerius.\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1454, \"end\": 1465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.999968710661719, \"rank\": 3.1288944247629376e-05, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 1481, \"end\": 1486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9940577675347285, \"rank\": 0.005277742352251819, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWith this act, we are setting a clear standard: sex should always be consensual and equal.\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone is acting criminally if they know\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094or should have known\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094that the other person does not want to do something but continues regardless,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Ye\\u00c5\\u009filg\\u00c3\\u00b6z-Zegerius.\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1811, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But at the time van de Velde committed his crime, theDutch Criminal Codedefined rapeonlyas forcing sex by an act of violence or any other act or by threat of violence or threat of any other act.\", \"from\": 1813, \"to\": 2007, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1829, \"end\": 1841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999795909488899, \"rank\": 2.0409467432898144e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather than requiring mutual consent, the code defined all sex as legal unless there was violence or the threat of violence.\\u00c2  If a person was convicted of rape by this standard, the maximum prison term was 12 years.\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sexually penetrating a person who was unconscious, or incapable of saying no, or otherwise unable to resist was considered a lesser crime.\", \"from\": 2226, \"to\": 2364, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It carried a maximum prison sentence of eight years.\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The maximum sentence for raping a child between the ages of 12 and 16 was eight years.\", \"from\": 2419, \"to\": 2505, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was illegal but not explicitly defined in the code as rape.\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Raping a child under 12 carried a maximum sentence of 12 years.\", \"from\": 2570, \"to\": 2633, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was also not explicitly defined as rape.\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sexually abusing your own child, foster child or any other minor under your control carried a maximum sentence of six years.\", \"from\": 2681, \"to\": 2805, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The new law both increases penalties and removes the requirement of force.\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s progress, obviously, but also: Consent has been a legal requirement in the Netherlands for 28 days.\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2990, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2966, \"end\": 2977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.999968710661719, \"rank\": 3.1288944247629376e-05, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So when Dutch officials selected van de Velde, painting any outrage over that selection as a media creation, and describing van de Velde as \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009can exemplary professional and human being,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d they are not simply justifying something unjustifiable.\", \"from\": 2992, \"to\": 3236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3000, \"end\": 3005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9940577675347285, \"rank\": 0.005277742352251819, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3025, \"end\": 3037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999795909488899, \"rank\": 2.0409467432898144e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}, {\"begin\": 3116, \"end\": 3128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999795909488899, \"rank\": 2.0409467432898144e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are reflecting how Dutch law has viewed the crime of rape.\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3261, \"end\": 3266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9940577675347285, \"rank\": 0.005277742352251819, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S. athletic federations, of course, have their own shameful history of ignoring or failing to address allegations and even incidents of\\u00c2\\u00a0sexual abuse.\", \"from\": 3302, \"to\": 3454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So it is fair to wonder if the U.S. would allow an American van de Velde to compete.\", \"from\": 3455, \"to\": 3539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3506, \"end\": 3514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999636170294, \"rank\": 3.553360198413158e-08, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no way to know for sure.\", \"from\": 3541, \"to\": 3574, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the U.S. Olympic & Paralympic Committee does now have a mechanism for banning coaches or athletes like van de Velde: The U.S. Center for Safesport regularly disciplines athletes and coaches for unprofessional or criminal conduct.\", \"from\": 3575, \"to\": 3808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3682, \"end\": 3694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999795909488899, \"rank\": 2.0409467432898144e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the 2021 Olympics, Safesport suspended fencer Alen Hadzic, who faced several allegations of sexual assault.\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3863, \"end\": 3874, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Fencing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alen Hadzic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Fencing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Fencing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An arbitrator overturned the suspension, andHedzic went to Tokyoas an alternate.\", \"from\": 3925, \"to\": 4005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was not allowed to live in the athletes\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 village (van de Velde is not living in the village in Paris).\", \"from\": 4006, \"to\": 4113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4061, \"end\": 4073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999795909488899, \"rank\": 2.0409467432898144e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}, {\"begin\": 4106, \"end\": 4111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999158717, \"rank\": 8.409926064809756e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now Hadzic is on Safesport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099spermanently ineligible list.\", \"from\": 4114, \"to\": 4172, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe are deeply concerned that anyone convicted of sexually assaulting a minor could participate in the 2024 Olympic Games,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Ju\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099Riese Col\\u00c3\\u00b3n, SafeSport\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Chief Executive Office.\", \"from\": 4174, \"to\": 4363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4340, \"end\": 4355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chief_Executive_of_Hong_Kong\", \"score\": 0.9999973556553816, \"rank\": 2.64435055884089e-06, \"text\": \"Chief Executive\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chief_Executive_of_Hong_Kong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chief_Executive_of_Hong_Kong\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis kind of criminal conviction\\u00c2\\u00a0would violate the U.S. Center for SafeSport Code.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Van de Velde is 29 now, a husband and father; his victim is 22.\", \"from\": 4364, \"to\": 4518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time of sentencing, the court heard testimony that she had been self-harming since the incident.\", \"from\": 4519, \"to\": 4622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The judgetoldvan de Velde: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe emotional harm that has been caused to this child is enormous.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  In a 2018interviewwith Dutch broadcaster NOS, van de Velde called the rape \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cthe biggest mistake of my young life,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and said \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t reverse it, so I have to live with the consequences.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u00a6 I can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t get around it.\", \"from\": 4623, \"to\": 4945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4747, \"end\": 4752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9940577675347285, \"rank\": 0.005277742352251819, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4765, \"end\": 4768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nederlandse_Omroep_Stichting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8961066656899908e-15, \"text\": \"NOS\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nederlandse_Omroep_Stichting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nederlandse_Omroep_Stichting\"}, {\"begin\": 4770, \"end\": 4782, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999795909488899, \"rank\": 2.0409467432898144e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I can also keep blaming myself a hundred thousand times for it happening and how it happened.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  He said he thought the girl was older when he first met her online, and when she said she was 12, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was really shocked, so I immediately broke off contact.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d But then he resumed communication, and he decided to go to England.\", \"from\": 4946, \"to\": 5273, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5265, \"end\": 5272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9856413321354742, \"rank\": 0.0141783463409592, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI booked that ticket in the morning and flew out in the afternoon.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  He said that when he was 19, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was sort of lost.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  He said that if he could go back and speak to his 19-year-old self, he would say, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cSeek help.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Today, Dutch authorities hear a man who is sorry and deserves a second chance.\", \"from\": 5274, \"to\": 5582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5511, \"end\": 5516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.9940577675347285, \"rank\": 0.005277742352251819, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But you might just see a sorry excuse for a man.\", \"from\": 5583, \"to\": 5631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 5633, \"to\": 5659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Michael Rosenberg is a senior writer for Sports Illustrated, covering any and all sports.\", \"from\": 5660, \"to\": 5813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5724, \"end\": 5741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Rosenberg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.682351541016675e-16, \"text\": \"Michael Rosenberg\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Rosenberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Rosenberg\"}, {\"begin\": 5765, \"end\": 5783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.525683270845831e-22, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He writes columns, profiles and feature stories and has covered almost every major sporting event.\", \"from\": 5814, \"to\": 5912, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He joined SI in 2012 after working at the Detroit Free Press for 13 years, eight of them as a columnist.\", \"from\": 5913, \"to\": 6017, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5955, \"end\": 5973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Detroit_Free_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Detroit Free Press\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Detroit_Free_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Detroit_Free_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rosenberg is the author of \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWar As They Knew It: Woody Hayes, Bo Schembechler and America in a Time of Unrest.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Several of his stories also have been published in collections of the year\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s best sportswriting.\", \"from\": 6018, \"to\": 6232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6018, \"end\": 6027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julius_and_Ethel_Rosenberg\", \"score\": 0.9999999323990801, \"rank\": 6.76011150010664e-08, \"text\": \"Rosenberg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julius_and_Ethel_Rosenberg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julius_and_Ethel_Rosenberg\"}, {\"begin\": 6082, \"end\": 6097, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bo_Schembechler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bo Schembechler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bo_Schembechler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bo_Schembechler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is married with three children.\", \"from\": 6233, \"to\": 6267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00c2\\u00a9 2026ABG-SI LLC-SPORTS ILLUSTRATED IS A REGISTERED TRADEMARK OF ABG-SI LLC.\", \"from\": 6269, \"to\": 6346, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"- All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 6347, \"to\": 6369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only.\", \"from\": 6370, \"to\": 6446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Sports Illustrated or its affiliates, licensees and related brands.\", \"from\": 6447, \"to\": 6641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6574, \"end\": 6592, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.525683270845831e-22, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit.\", \"from\": 6642, \"to\": 6730, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\", \"from\": 6731, \"to\": 6863, \"entities\": []}]}"